 media has its perks&#8230;</p></div></a></div><div class="hide-for-medium large-4 columns article-summary"><a href="http://dailyreckoning.com/worse-than-2008/"><div class="article-image"><img src="http://dweaay7e22a7h.cloudfront.net/dr-content_3/uploads/2014/11/Umbrella-Pig-225x125.jpg" data-img-src="http://dweaay7e22a7h.cloudfront.net/dr-content_3/uploads/2016/02/Bewehrungsbinder_DF16_web-225x125.jpg"></div><div class="inner-text"><h3>Worse Than 2008</h3><div class="meta-text"><p> By Bill Bonner Posted February 12, 2016</p></div><p>In 2008, a ton of rebar cost about 5,500 renminbi ($836). Now, it costs barely 2,000 renminbi ($304) – the lowest price&hellip;</p></div></a></div></div></div></li><li><a href="http://dailyreckoning.com/author/jrickards">James Rickards</a><div class="featured-articles"><div class="row collapse"><div class="small-12 medium-6 large-4 columns article-summary"><a href="http://dailyreckoning.com/helicopter-money-gathers-momentum/"><div class="article-image"><img src="http://dweaay7e22a7h.cloudfront.net/dr-content_3/uploads/2014/11/Umbrella-Pig-225x125.jpg" data-img-src="http://dweaay7e22a7h.cloudfront.net/dr-content_3/uploads/2016/02/HelicopterMoneyHero-225x125.png"></div><div class="inner-text"><h3>Helicopter Money Gathers Momentum</h3><div class="meta-text"><p> By James Rickards Posted February 17, 2016</p></div><p>Can you hear those rotors yet? Jim Rickards shows you why the global elites can only resort to helicopter money to jump-start&hellip;</p></div></a></div><div class="small-12 medium-6 large-4 columns article-summary"><a href="http://dailyreckoning.com/heres-where-nirp-leads/"><div class="article-image"><img src="http://dweaay7e22a7h.cloudfront.net/dr-content_3/uploads/2014/11/Umbrella-Pig-225x125.jpg" data-img-src="http://dweaay7e22a7h.cloudfront.net/dr-content_3/uploads/2016/02/1280px-Bank_of_Japan_2010-225x125.jpg"></div><div class="inner-text"><h3>Here&#039;s Where NIRP Leads...</h3><div class="meta-text"><p> By James Rickards Posted February 16, 2016</p></div><p>Thus far, the reaction from the financial markets is that NIRP is not good. Stock markets are spooked, and investors are piling&hellip;</p></div></a></div><div class="hide-for-medium large-4 columns article-summary"><a href="http://dailyreckoning.com/markets-the-fed-and-asymmetry/"><div class="article-image"><img src="http://dweaay7e22a7h.cloudfront.net/dr-content_3/uploads/2014/11/Umbrella-Pig-225x125.jpg" data-img-src="http://dweaay7e22a7h.cloudfront.net/dr-content_3/uploads/2016/02/shutterstock_351795326-225x125.jpg"></div><div class="inner-text"><h3>Markets, the Fed, and Asymmetry</h3><div class="meta-text"><p> By James Rickards Posted February 10, 2016</p></div><p>Jim Rickards shows you why the “plunge protection team” will be AWOL short of the S&#038;P hitting 1,690 by next week, and&hellip;</p></div></a></div></div></div></li><li><a href="http://dailyreckoning.com/author/dstockman">David Stockman</a><div class="featured-articles"><div class="row collapse"><div class="small-12 medium-6 large-4 columns article-summary"><a href="http://dailyreckoning.com/why-keynesian-market-wreckers-are-now-coming-for-your-benjamins/"><div class="article-image"><img src="http://dweaay7e22a7h.cloudfront.net/dr-content_3/uploads/2014/11/Umbrella-Pig-225x125.jpg" data-img-src="http://dweaay7e22a7h.cloudfront.net/dr-content_3/uploads/2016/02/800px-100_USD_1934-225x125.jpg"></div><div class="inner-text"><h3>Why Keynesian Market Wreckers are Now Coming for Your Benjamins</h3><div class="meta-text"><p> By David Stockman Posted February 18, 2016</p></div><p>Suddenly every NIRP advocate on the planet has joined the campaign to abolish large bills including the Benjamin Franklin here and the&hellip;</p></div></a></div><div class="small-12 medium-6 large-4 columns article-summary"><a href="http://dailyreckoning.com/simple-janet-the-monetary-android-with-a-broken-flash-drive/"><div class="article-image"><img src="http://dweaay7e22a7h.cloudfront.net/dr-